    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-21T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-21T18:00:00-05:00" n="470"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.50a/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sussdorff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-21T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 21, 1923—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. The Department desires you to inform the Minister for Foreign Affairs of
                    Luxemburg that it is the intention of the Government of the United States to
                    accredit as its representative near the Grand Ducal Government the American
                    diplomatic representative at Brussels <pb facs="0645" n="521" xml:id="pg_521"/>
                    instead of the representative at The Hague, as has heretofore been the practice;
                    and also that to this end you are directed to request the <hi rend="italic"
                        >agrément</hi> of Mr. Fletcher, whom the President desires to appoint as
                    Minister to Luxemburg. If the Government of Luxemburg request to be informed
                    through what channels it may communicate with the Department during the interval
                    before Mr. Fletcher presents his letter of credence,<note n="1" xml:id="d470fn1"
                        >Mr. Fletcher presented his letter of credence on Oct. 29, 1923.</note> you
                    may reply that it may continue to send its communications through the Legation
                    at The Hague and addressed to yourself as Chargé d’Affaires ad interim. This
                    duty will not entitle you to additional compensation and you will not visit
                    Luxemburg without the express authorization of the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
